<title type="html"><![CDATA[Do you Order Righteousness of the People and Forget Yourselves? – Ibn Rajab]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=663&amp;p=706#p706"><![CDATA[
Ibn Rajab[1] rahimahullaah mentions in his <span style="color: #0000FF"><em>‘Lataaiful-Ma`aarif'</em></span>:<br /><br />“A man said to Ibn Abbaas radiyAllaahu `anhumaa: “I want to enjoin the good and forbid the evil.”<br /><br />So he said to him: “If you do not fear these three ayaat exposing you; then do so. Otherwise, begin with yourself.”<br />Then he recited:<br />أَتَأْمُرُونَ النَّاسَ بِالْبِرِّ وَتَنسَوْنَ أَنفُسَكُمْ<br /><br />“Do you order righteousness of the people and forget yourselves.&quot; [Sooratul Baqarah; (2):44]<br /><br />And His saying – He the Most High:<br />لِمَ تَقُولُونَ مَا لَا تَفْعَلُونَ كَبُرَ مَقْتًا عِندَ اللَّهِ أَن تَقُولُوا مَا لَا تَفْعَلُونَ<br /><br />“Why do you say that which you do not do? It is most hateful to Allaah that you say that which you do not do. [Sooratus-Saff; (61):2-3]<br /><br />And His saying – regarding the story of Shu`ayb `alayhis-Salaam – (where he said to his people):<br />وَمَا أُرِيدُ أَنْ أُخَالِفَكُمْ إِلَىٰ مَا أَنْهَاكُمْ عَنْهُ<br /><br />“And I do not intend to differ from you in that which I have forbidden you.” [Sooratul-Hood; (11):88]<br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF"><br />[Source: ‘Lataaiful Ma`aarif fil-Mawaasim al-`Aam min al-Wadhaaif’ of Ibn Rajab; al-Maktab al-Islaamee edtn. pge. 41]</span></strong><br /><br /><br />[1] Zayn ud-Deen Abil Faraj Abdur-Rahmaan bin Shihaab ud-Deen Ahmad bin Rajab al-Hanbalee, al-Baghdaadee, ad-Dimishqee [736H-795H] – rahimahullaah –<br /><br />Source: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://saadburbank.com/2015/02/24/do-you-order-righteousness-of-the-people-and-forget-yourselves-ibn-rajab/">http://saadburbank.com/2015/02/24/do-yo ... ibn-rajab/</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> — Sun Nov 20, 2016 10:57 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
